    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan with a matching lid with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>over&nbsp;a medium heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>shallot</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>garlic</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 6-8 min or until slightly browned, then add the&nbsp;<strong>cumin</strong>,<strong> cayenne </strong>(Can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and<strong>&nbsp;smoked paprika</strong>&nbsp;and cook for 10-20 sec</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the&nbsp;<strong>stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>&nbsp;</strong>in 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
